------------------------------------------------
			VIRTUAL ENVIRONMENT:
------------------------------------------------

-----------------------------------------------------
List Virtualenvs:
-----------------------------------------------------
OPTION (1):
lsvirtualenv -b 	-OR- 	lsvirtualenv -l


OPTION (2):
ls ~/virtualenvironment/


==========================================================================================
METHOD 1:
---------

------------------------------------------------
Install VirtualEnv:
$ export WORKON_HOME=$HOME/.virtualenvs
$ source /usr/local/bin/virtualenvwrapper.sh
$ source ~/.bashrc

------------------------------------------------
Create the Environment:
$ mkvirtualenv env_name
-OR-
$ mkvirtualenv env_name -p python2
-OR-
$ mkvirtualenv env_name -p python3

------------------------------------------------
Activate:
$ workon env_name

------------------------------------------------
Deactivate the Environment:
$ deactivate


==========================================================================================
METHOD 2:
---------

------------------------------------------------
Install Python3 Enviroments:
$ sudo apt-get install -y python3-venv

------------------------------------------------
Make directory to work in Enviroment:
$ mkdir environments
$ cd environments

------------------------------------------------
Create an environment in this folder:
$ python3 -m venv my_env

------------------------------------------------
Activate the Enviroment:
$ source my_env/bin/activate

-------------------
$ deactivate


==========================================================================================
METHOD 3:
---------

------------------------------------------------
Install virtualenv:
$ sudo -H apt-get install python3-pip python3-dev build-essential
$ sudo -H pip3 install virtualenv virtualenvwrapper
$ sudo -H pip3 install --upgrade pip


==========================================================================================
